### Capture screenshot to in-memory buffer using Playwright

Source: https://github.com/microsoft/playwright/blob/main/docs/src/screenshots.md

This example illustrates how to take a screenshot and retrieve its raw byte data into a buffer, rather than saving it directly to a file. The buffer can then be post-processed or encoded (e.g., to Base64). Requires a Playwright page instance. The output is a byte array or buffer containing image data.

```js
const buffer = await page.screenshot();
console.log(buffer.toString('base64'));
```

```java
byte[] buffer = page.screenshot();
System.out.println(Base64.getEncoder().encodeToString(buffer));
```

```python async
# Capture into Image
screenshot_bytes = await page.screenshot()
print(base64.b64encode(screenshot_bytes).decode())
```

```python sync
screenshot_bytes = page.screenshot()
print(base64.b64encode(screenshot_bytes).decode())
```

```csharp
var bytes = await page.ScreenshotAsync();
Console.WriteLine(Convert.ToBase64String(bytes));
```

