### Retrieve Recent Network Requests and Console Messages in Playwright

Source: https://context7.com/microsoft/playwright/llms.txt

Illustrates how to access historical network requests, console messages, and page errors that occurred on a page using Playwright's `page.requests()`, `page.consoleMessages()`, and `page.pageErrors()`. This is useful for debugging and asserting page behavior after interactions.

```javascript
test('retrieve recent requests and console messages', async ({ page }) => {
  await page.goto('https://example.com');
  await page.getByRole('button', { name: 'Load Data' }).click();

  // Get most recent network requests
  const requests = page.requests();
  console.log('Recent requests:', requests.map(r => r.url()));

  // Get console messages from the page
  const messages = page.consoleMessages();
  console.log('Console messages:', messages.map(m => m.text()));

  // Get page errors
  const errors = page.pageErrors();
  if (errors.length > 0) {
    console.error('Page errors:', errors.map(e => e.message));
  }
});
```

