### Locator.screenshot API

Source: https://github.com/microsoft/playwright/blob/main/docs/src/api/class-locator.md

Takes a screenshot of the element matching the locator. The element is scrolled into view before the screenshot is taken.

```APIDOC
## Locator.screenshot

### Description
Takes a screenshot of the element matching the locator. The method waits for actionability checks, then scrolls the element into view before capturing the screenshot. If the element is detached from the DOM, an error is thrown. The screenshot is clipped to the element's size and position.

### Method
`screenshot(options?: { animations?: 'disabled' | 'auto', path?: string })`

### Parameters
#### Path Parameters
None

#### Query Parameters
None

#### Request Body
None

### Options
- **animations** (string: 'disabled' | 'auto') - Optional - Controls whether animations are enabled during the screenshot. Defaults to 'auto'.
- **path** (string) - Optional - Saves the screenshot to the specified file path.

### Request Example
```javascript
await page.getByRole('link').screenshot();
await page.getByRole('link').screenshot({ animations: 'disabled', path: 'link.png' });
```

### Response
#### Success Response (Buffer)
- **screenshotBuffer** (Buffer) - The buffer containing the captured screenshot data.

#### Response Example
(Binary data representing the screenshot image)
```

