### Method: Page.screenshot

Source: https://github.com/microsoft/playwright/blob/main/docs/src/api/class-page.md

Captures a screenshot of the current page and returns it as a buffer. Various options are available to customize the screenshot.

```APIDOC
## METHOD CALL Page.screenshot

### Description
Captures a screenshot of the current page and returns the buffer with the captured image.

### Method
Client Method Call

### Endpoint
N/A

### Parameters
#### Options
- **timeout** (number) - Optional - Maximum time in milliseconds for the operation to complete.
- **fullPage** (boolean) - Optional - When true, takes a screenshot of the full scrollable page. Defaults to false.
- **clip** (object) - Optional - An object specifying the clipping region of the page to screenshot.
  - **x** (number) - Required - X-coordinate of top-left corner of the clip region.
  - **y** (number) - Required - Y-coordinate of top-left corner of the clip region.
  - **width** (number) - Required - Width of the clip region.
  - **height** (number) - Required - Height of the clip region.

### Request Example
```javascript
const screenshotBuffer = await page.screenshot({ path: 'screenshot.png', fullPage: true });
```

### Response
#### Success Response
- (Buffer) - The buffer with the captured screenshot image data.

#### Response Example
```
<Buffer 89 50 4e 47 0d 0a 1a 0a ...> (image data)
```
```

