### Attaching a Screenshot to Test Report (Playwright, JS)

Source: https://github.com/microsoft/playwright/blob/main/docs/src/test-api/class-testinfo.md

This Playwright example shows how to capture a screenshot and attach it to the test report using `testInfo.attach()`. The screenshot is passed as a `Buffer` along with its content type. This feature is crucial for visual regression testing or documenting UI states during test failures.

```javascript
import { test, expect } from '@playwright/test';

test('basic test', async ({ page }, testInfo) => {
  await page.goto('https://playwright.dev');
  const screenshot = await page.screenshot();
  await testInfo.attach('screenshot', { body: screenshot, contentType: 'image/png' });
});
```
